# @convo-lang/cli

Binary distribution package for the Convo-Lang CLI.

This package provides the `convo` command as prebuilt binaries for supported platforms. It is intended for users who want to install and run the Convo-Lang CLI without building it from source.

## Install

``` bash
npm install -g @convo-lang/cli
```

Or run it without installing globally:

``` bash
npx @convo-lang/cli --help
```

## Usage

``` bash
convo --help
```

Run a Convo-Lang file:

``` bash
convo ./chat.convo
```

Run inline Convo-Lang code:

``` bash
convo --inline "> user\nTell me a joke"
```

Start the REPL:

``` bash
convo --repl
```

## Notes

- This package is a binary wrapper/distribution package.
- The CLI implementation lives in the Convo-Lang monorepo.
- Use `convo --help` to see the full list of supported arguments and examples.

## Related packages

- `convo-lang`
- `@convo-lang/convo-lang`
```
